<eesti>Metsateatis </eesti>
<inglise>Forest notification </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Metsaomanik on kohustatud asukohaj&auml;rgsele keskkonnateenistusele esitama metsateatise, mis sisaldab andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The owner of a forest is required to submit a forest notification to the environmental authority of the location of the forest which contains information on: </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </inglise>
<eesti>1) kavandatud raie liikidest vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-dele 13-14, 16-19 ja 34, metsauuendust&ouml;&ouml;dest, metsakuivenduss&uuml;steemide ja metsateede ehitamisest ja uuendamisest ning nende t&ouml;&ouml;de k&auml;igus loodus- ja muinsuskaitse n&otilde;uete tagamisest (kaasa arvatud v&otilde;tmebiotoopide s&auml;ilitamine); </eesti>
<inglise>1) the types of cutting planned pursuant to &sect;&sect; 13-14, 16-19 and 34 of this Act, reforestation works, construction and renewal of forest draining systems and forest roads, and measures to fulfil nature and heritage conservation requirements (including the maintenance of key biotopes) in the course of this work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) metsakahjustustest. </eesti>
<inglise>2) forest damages. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 loetletud andmed esitatakse asukohaj&auml;rgsele keskkonnateenistusele v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat enne t&ouml;&ouml;de alustamist ja punktis 2 nimetatud informatsioon kohe p&auml;rast seda, kui omanik sai teada v&otilde;i pidi teada saama metsa kahjustamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The information specified in clause (1) 1) of this section shall be submitted to the environmental authority of the location of the forest at least two weeks before commencing work, and the information specified in clause 2) of this Act immediately after the owner becomes or should have become aware of the forest damage. </inglise>
<eesti>Metsateatis loetakse esitatuks selle asukohaj&auml;rgses keskkonnateenistuses registreerimise p&auml;evast v&otilde;i posti panemise p&auml;evast postitempli j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>A forest notification is deemed to be submitted as of the date of its registration in the environmental authority of the location of the forest, or the date of posting on the postage frank. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) F&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust metsaomanik ei esita metsateatist: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The owner of forest who is a natural person shall not submit a forest notification: </inglise>
<eesti>1) oma metsast raiutud tuuleheite, tuule- ja lumemurru kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) with regard to windfallen wood, windbreakage and snowbreakage cut in his or her forest; </inglise>
<eesti>2) metsamaa iga hektari kohta aastas 1 tm muu puidu raiumise kohta juhul, kui &uuml;ldkogus ei &uuml;leta 50 tm aastas. </eesti>
<inglise>2) with regard to 1 solid cubic metre of other timber cut per every hectare of forest land per year if the total volume does not exceed 50 solid cubic metres per year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kahe n&auml;dala jooksul teatise saamisest asukohaj&auml;rgne keskkonnateenistus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Within two weeks as of the receipt of a notification, the environmental authority of the location of the forest shall: </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </inglise>
<eesti>1) keelab kavandatud tegevuse, kui see on vastuolus &otilde;igusaktiga; </eesti>
<inglise>1) prohibit the planned activity if it is contrary to legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhib teatise esitaja t&auml;helepanu sellele, et kavandatav tegevus ei vasta metsamajandamiskavale v&otilde;i metsa majandamise soovitustele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) draw the attention of the person submitting the report to the fact that the planned activity does not comply with a forest management plan or forest management recommendations; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teeb teatise esitajale ettepaneku viia kavandatav tegevus koosk&otilde;lla &otilde;igusaktiga, metsamajandamiskavaga v&otilde;i metsa majandamise soovitustega ja esitada uus teatis. </eesti>
<inglise>3) make a proposal to the person submitting the notification to bring the planned activity into conformity with legislation, the forest management plan or forest management recommendations and to submit a new notification. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Metsateatise esitajal on &otilde;igus alustada metsateatises kavandatud t&ouml;id, kui asukohaj&auml;rgne keskkonnateenistus ei ole kahe n&auml;dala jooksul teatise esitamisest keelanud teatises kavandatud tegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The person submitting a forest notification has the right to commence works planned in the forest notification if the environmental authority of the location of the forest has not prohibited the activity planned in the notification within two weeks after the submission of the notification. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 95, 843) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Metsateatise vormi, edastamise ja l&auml;bivaatamise korra kehtestab keskkonnaminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of the Environment shall establish the form and procedure for submission and review of forest notifications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Omaniku &otilde;igused ja kohustused metsa majandamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and obligations of owner in forest management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Metsaomanikul on &otilde;igus tulekaitse kaalutlustel, metsa &ouml;kos&uuml;steemi v&otilde;i sihtide, teede ja teiste rajatiste kaitseks peatada v&otilde;i keelata oma metsa, sihtide, teede ja teiste rajatiste kasutamine, kui ilmastikutingimused ei v&otilde;imalda metsa v&otilde;i nimetatud rajatisi kasutada ilma metsa v&otilde;i rajatisi kahjustamata v&otilde;i ohtu seadmata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The owner of a forest has the right to suspend or prohibit the use of his or her forest, rides, roads and other constructions for the purpose of fire protection, the protection of the ecosystem of the forest or the protection of the rides, roads and other constructions, if the meteorological conditions do not allow to use the forest or the specified constructions without damaging or endangering the forest or the constructions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Metsaomanik on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner of a forest is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tagama metsa uuenemise v&otilde;imalused ja metsa uuendamise; </eesti>
<inglise>1) ensure the conditions for the regeneration of the forest, and reforestation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;lgima metsa seisundit, kaitsma metsa kasvutingimuste halvenemise, kahjurite ja haiguste, prahistamise ja tulekahjude eest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) monitor the condition of the forest, protect the forest against the deterioration of site conditions, pests, diseases, littering or fires; </inglise>
<eesti>3) majandama ja lubama oma metsa majandada &uuml;ksnes sellisel viisil, mis ei ohusta metsa kui &ouml;kos&uuml;steemi ega kahjusta genofondi, metsamulda ja veere&zcaron;iimi, metsa uuenemise ja uuendamise tingimusi, ei loo eeldusi tuulekahjustuste tekkeks, seenhaiguste ja putukkahjurite levikuks ning on koosk&otilde;las metsa s&auml;&auml;stliku kasutamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) manage and permit his or her forest to be managed only in such a way which does not endanger the forest as an ecosystem or damage the gene pool, forest soil or water regime, the conditions for forest regeneration and reforestation, does not allow wind damages, the spread of fungus diseases or pests and is in accordance with the principles of the sustainable use of forest; </inglise>
<eesti>4) metsa k&otilde;rvalsaaduste varumisel rakendama ja lubama rakendada &uuml;ksnes selliseid varumisviise, mis ei kahjusta k&otilde;rvalsaaduste nagu marjad, seened ja ravimtaimed saagikust; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the gathering of forest by-products, apply and permit the application of only such gathering methods which do not damage the productivity of such by-products as berries, mushrooms and herbs; </inglise>
<eesti>5) esitama statistilised aruanded vastavalt riikliku statistika seadusele (RT I 1997, 51, 822) ja metsateatise. </eesti>
<inglise>5) submit statistical returns pursuant to the Official Statistics Act (RT I 1997, 51, 822), and forest notifications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punkti 3 n&otilde;uded ei laiene metsadele, mille kasutamise viisiks on riigikaitse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements of clause (2) 3) of this section do not apply to forests which are used for national defence. </inglise>
